                                עַל־רֵיעֲכֶם </foreign>
                            ‘and you dig a pit for your friend’, added interlinearly by another
                            hand. See also next footnote.</note>
                        <note xml:id="fn5" type="footnote">An alternative translation to <emph>da
                                ʒuɣur qazasiz dostlarynyz istine</emph>, the equivalent of BHeb.
                                <foreign xml:lang="he" style="unicode-bidi: embed;">וְתִכְר֗וּ
                                עַל־רֵיעֲכֶם </foreign>
                            ‘and you dig a pit for your friend’.</note>
